## §Cadence Rule 2 — ADR Merge → Sister-Issue Dispatch Atomicity

Codifies the orphan-impl cadence gap surfaced by AtilCalculator's ADR-0060
forward-port never landing (template PR #97 + #108 + #110 merged 2026-07-14/15;
AtilCalculator sister work never opened). Owner manual fix applied 3 times to
`scripts/dev-studio-start.sh:149` before persistence requested.

**Rule**: When ANY `docs/decisions/ADR-NNNN-*.md` PR merges to `main` (or
sister-pattern RETRO/Issue body lists tracked sister issues), the SAME TURN
MUST also `@`-mention-dispatch each listed sister issue to its `agent:*`
owner — OR the turn is recorded as **INCOMPLETE** in `/var/log/dev-studio/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/auto-claim.log`.

**Atomic sub-steps** (per ADR-0015 4-flag discipline + ADR-0024 verdict-by):

1. **Cross-repo sister detection** — `gh pr view <N> --json body --jq '.body'`
   must be parsed for `Closes #X` / `Refs #X` anchors referencing issues in
   the SAME org (`atilproject/*`). Sister issues = those NOT yet closed.
2. **Per-sister dispatch** — for each unclosed sister issue: `gh issue comment <X> --body "@<agent-role> dispatch: ADR-NNNN merged in <YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ>; your lane is <lane>; Closes #X" --repo <repo>`. Order: tester (d-test) → developer (impl) → orchestrator (board sync).
3. **State emission** — write `auto-claim.log` line: `[cadence-rule-2] ADR-NNNN merged → dispatched <count> sister issues: #X1, #X2, #X3`. If count == 0, log `[cadence-rule-2] ADR-NNNN merged → no sister issues (INCOMPLETE-check passed but no work to dispatch)`.
4. **Retrospective lens** — if a `[cadence-rule-2] INCOMPLETE` flag is observed
   in `auto-claim.log` for the same ADR within 7 days, sprint retro MUST
   file a RETRO entry capturing the gap.

**Origin**: Sprint 30 KAPI hotfix (cycle ~#2776, owner directive 2026-07-17
~08:34Z). Sister-pattern: `[[cadence-rule-1]]` (ADR-0055 — `d-number allocation atomic`).

**Domain lens applicability:** primarily (a) data flow + (c) API contract.
Sister-patterns: TD-016 (silent-skip), TD-030 (auto-gen file refs), RETRO-024
